# MCMC parameters
n_adapt = 1000
iter = 50000
# Example nodes
methyl = "cg00287636"
metab = "gctof_33"
temp = pair_data[,c("T1Dgroup",methyl,metab)]
temp = temp[complete.cases(temp),]
# Data (X[,1] must be methylation and X[,2] must be metabolite)
y = as.numeric(temp$T1Dgroup) - 1
X = temp[,c(methyl,metab)]
N = nrow(X)
# JAGS
jags_data = list(y=y,X=X,N=N)
mod = jags.model("./code/networks/omics_to_t1d_methyl_to_metab.jags",
                 data = jags_data, n.adapt = n_adapt,n.chains = 2)
## Compiling model graph
##    Resolving undeclared variables
##    Allocating nodes
## Graph information:
##    Observed stochastic nodes: 292
##    Unobserved stochastic nodes: 6
##    Total graph size: 1249
## 
## Initializing model
# MCMC
samples = coda.samples(mod,n.iter = iter,thin = 20,
                       variable.names = c("beta0","beta1","beta2","gamma0","gamma1"))
# Output
output = MCMCsummary(samples, 
                     params = c("beta0","beta1","beta2","gamma0","gamma1"),
                     Rhat = F,
                     n.eff = F,
                     HPD = T,
                     hpd_prob = 0.8,
                     digits = 3)
MCMCtrace(samples,pdf = F,iter = iter - n_adapt)
